chai assertion library: https://www.chaijs.com/api/bdd

chai's extensibility allows you to create custom assertions and plugins tailored to your project's specific needs.

you can define your custom assertions using chai's API

chai has a vibrant ecosystem of plugins that extend its functionality.

these plugins cover various use cases, e.g. 
  HTTP assertions, 
  asynchronous testing,
  assertion extensions


should and expect
  BDD provides an easy and readable language style via should and expect


assert
  TDD provides a comparatively classical approach using assert


chai supports method chaining, allowing you to make multiple assertions in a single statement for more concise test code.
